def _match_one(filter_part, dct):
    comparison_value = None
    if '<' in filter_part:
        key, value = filter_part.split('<')
        comparison_value = value.strip()
        return dct.get(key) < comparison_value
    elif '<=' in filter_part:
        key, value = filter_part.split('<=')
        comparison_value = value.strip()
        return dct.get(key) <= comparison_value
    elif '>' in filter_part:
        key, value = filter_part.split('>')
        comparison_value = value.strip()
        return dct.get(key) > comparison_value
    elif '>=' in filter_part:
        key, value = filter_part.split('>=')
        comparison_value = value.strip()
        return dct.get(key) >= comparison_value
    elif '=' in filter_part:
        key, value = filter_part.split('=')
        comparison_value = value.strip()
        return dct.get(key) == comparison_value
    elif '!=' in filter_part:
        key, value = filter_part.split('!=')
        comparison_value = value.strip()
        return dct.get(key) != comparison_value
    else:
        raise ValueError('Invalid filter part %r' % filter_part)
